citation.case_name: Commercial Barge Lines, Inc. v. United States

html:
359 U.S. 342

79 S.Ct. 896

3 L.Ed.2d 927

COMMERCIAL BARGE LINES, INC., et al.
v.
UNITED STATES et al.

No. 721.

Supreme Court of the United States

April 27, 1959

Messrs. Dudley B. Tenney and Nuel D. Belnap, for appellants.

Solicitor General Rankin, Assistant Attorney General Hansen, and Messrs. Robert W. Ginnane and Charlie H. Johns, for the United States and Interstate Commerce Commission.

Messrs. Stuart B. Bradley, Carl Helmetag, Jr., J. D. Feeney, Harry C. Ames, R. Granville Curry, Frederick M. Dolan, Donald Macleay and Russell S. Bernhard, for carrier appellees.

PER CURIAM.

1

The motions to affirm are granted and the judgment is affirmed.
